<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12022a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12022a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12022a"> 22(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> vision always disappearing</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Et, ce disant, il donna un soufflet &agrave; l&apos;enfant. Puis il le saisit par le bras et le conduisit vers l&apos;autel pour lui faire honte devant les p&egrave;lerins qui priaient toujours et qui n&apos;avaient pas <font color="green">[57]</font> tourn&eacute; la t&ecirc;te au bruit du soufflet. Drogon passa devant la statue sans s&apos;incliner. Il re&ccedil;ut aussit&ocirc;t, d&apos;une invisible main, un formidable soufflet qui claqua bruyamment dans l&apos;&eacute;glise et qui le renversa par terre, o&ugrave; il resta, quelques minutes, &eacute;tendu sans connaissance; tandis que Nicolas priait l&apos;Archange de toute son &acirc;me, car l&apos;enfant avait compris qu&apos;un &eacute;v&eacute;nement extraordinaire venait de s&apos;accomplir. Quand Drogon se releva, encore tout &eacute;tourdi, les trois p&egrave;lerins avaient disparu; or, toutes les portes &eacute;taient bien ferm&eacute;es! <font color="green">[And so saying, he gave a blow to the child. Then he seized him by the arm and led him to the altar to shame him before the pilgrims who were still praying and who had not [57]</font> turned their heads to the sound of the bellows. Drogon passed the statue without bowing. He received at once, with an invisible hand, a formidable bellows, which slammed loudly in the church, and knocked him to the ground, where he remained, for a few minutes, lying unconscious; while Nicholas prayed to the Archangel with all his soul, for the child had understood that an extraordinary event had just been accomplished. When Drogon got up again, still stunned, the three pilgrims had disappeared; but all the doors were closed!] <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 57-8 [Le ch&acirc;timent du sacristain Drogon]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
